# Operations System v1.0.0 Core

- Build a clean v1.0.0 rewrite from scratch. Do not refactor the old project in place.
- Treat the old OperationsSystem project as a business reference only, not an architectural source.
- Preserve correct business behavior while removing old technical debt, UI patterns, inconsistent naming, and client-specific logic.
- Use an API-first modular monolith: one deployable backend, clear module boundaries, vertical slices inside modules, and pragmatic CQRS.
- React web and the existing Android app must consume the same backend API and business rules.
- Public business endpoints start with `/api/v1`; do not expose unversioned business endpoints.
- Keep the API host thin. Business rules belong in domain models, value objects, domain services, or application handlers as appropriate.
- Modules must not reference another module's internals or DbContexts. Use contracts, read models, integration events, or the API surface for cross-module communication.
- Prefer simple, explicit code over clever abstractions. Add abstractions only when they remove real complexity or match an established local pattern.
- The old Blazor solution lives under `legacy/` in this repo and is read-only business reference. Read the relevant old files before rewriting a feature and cite which files you used.
- v1.0.0 is single-tenant. Do not build multi-tenant infrastructure, but do not bake in assumptions that would block adding tenancy later.
- The product is bilingual (Arabic and English) with full right-to-left support. Do not hardcode user-facing strings; keep them localizable on both backend and frontend.
- Store and exchange time in UTC; render in the user/operation time zone at the edges.
- For architecture-level changes, read `docs/architecture/operations-system-v1.md` first and keep decisions aligned with its decisions log.
- Track rewrite progress in `docs/architecture/migration-inventory.md` so strong old behavior is not lost.
- Do not introduce new technologies without updating `docs/architecture/operations-system-v1.md` and recording the decision.
- Add or update tests with meaningful business coverage for rewritten behavior.
